37
00:01:47,857 --> 00:01:49,281
Okay.

38
00:01:49,296 --> 00:01:51,753
They haven't armed the doors yet,
so you still have a chance.

39
00:01:51,767 --> 00:01:54,123
It's up to the captain now
and they're calling us back.

40
00:01:54,137 --> 00:01:56,323
Great, please let us know
soon as you hear anything.

41
00:01:56,338 --> 00:01:58,560
Sure, and for the future,
we recommend you arrive

42
00:01:58,576 --> 00:02:01,181
at the airport an hour and
a half before your flight,

43
00:02:01,197 --> 00:02:03,131
not, you know,
one minute after.

44
00:02:03,146 --> 00:02:05,112
Normally, I'm
incredibly responsible.

45
00:02:05,128 --> 00:02:07,140
I just had to go to court this
morning and get sentenced.

46
00:02:07,617 --> 00:02:09,703
Not that I'm a
criminal or anything.

47
00:02:09,717 --> 00:02:11,731
Yeah, he just jumped
a subway turnstile.

48
00:02:11,746 --> 00:02:15,022
You seem to have a lot of problems
with the rules of travel.

49
00:02:16,787 --> 00:02:17,912
Hello?

50
00:02:20,318 --> 00:02:22,743
Oh, that is great news.

51
00:02:22,758 --> 00:02:24,842
It's my mom--
she found her missing earring.

52
00:02:24,866 --> 00:02:26,952
Have a seat.
I'll call you when I hear something.

53
00:02:26,968 --> 00:02:28,943
Where was it?

54
00:02:28,978 --> 00:02:30,953
That thing better
have call waiting.

55
00:02:30,965 --> 00:02:33,332
Could you just call the firm
and explain what happened?

56
00:02:33,345 --> 00:02:36,841
It's down to three people
and I know they need to
make their decision today.

57
00:02:36,868 --> 00:02:40,232
I sort of feel my not showing up
might put me at a disadvantage.

58
00:02:41,305 --> 00:02:43,111
I'm so stupid.

59
00:02:43,125 --> 00:02:45,223
Why did I have to
jump that turnstile?

60
00:02:45,238 --> 00:02:47,923
Hey, don't be so
hard on yourself.

61
00:02:47,936 --> 00:02:50,800
And isn't this whole thing
really Barney's fault?

62
00:02:50,908 --> 00:02:54,070
<i>She had a point.
It was kind of Barney's fault.</i>

63
00:02:54,085 --> 00:02:56,362
<i>Let's back up a few months.</i>

64
00:02:56,568 --> 00:02:58,471
Oh, Marshall,
how's the broken toe?

65
00:02:58,488 --> 00:03:01,670
Oh, man, it kills.
You  want some aspirin, baby?

66
00:03:01,685 --> 00:03:04,293
You know I don't
believe in pain killers.

67
00:03:05,966 --> 00:03:08,161
Wow, your first broken bone.

68
00:03:08,176 --> 00:03:10,062
Kind of kills your whole
"Unbreakable" theory.

69
00:03:10,076 --> 00:03:12,773
Marshall used to think
he was indestructible.

70
00:03:12,787 --> 00:03:15,251
Well, it added up.
I've never broken anything.

71
00:03:15,265 --> 00:03:17,511
I've never been sick,
and when I need to,

72
00:03:17,525 --> 00:03:19,612
I can summon
incredible strength.

73
00:03:19,638 --> 00:03:22,190
Ted, tell her the story
of the really heavy door.

74
00:03:22,266 --> 00:03:25,473
There was a really heavy door.
He opened it.

75
00:03:25,695 --> 00:03:27,652
On one pull.

76
00:03:29,318 --> 00:03:32,172
Well, you must be really bummed, you're
not gonna be able to run tomorrow.

77
00:03:32,205 --> 00:03:33,580
Yeah. It sucks,

78
00:03:33,597 --> 00:03:36,960
all that work I put in training
for the marathon was a total waste.

79
00:03:36,978 --> 00:03:38,972
Training for a marathon.

80
00:03:39,818 --> 00:03:41,392
What?

81
00:03:41,405 --> 00:03:44,232
You don't need to train for a marathon.
You just run it.

82
00:03:44,348 --> 00:03:46,021
You're kidding, right?

83
00:03:46,035 --> 00:03:48,792
Not at all. I could run a
marathon anytime I wanted to.

84
00:03:48,946 --> 00:03:51,942
So like tomorrow, you think you
could wake up, roll out of bed,

85
00:03:51,956 --> 00:03:54,710
and just run the New
York City Marathon?
Absolutely.

86
00:03:54,727 --> 00:03:57,771
Barney, we're talking
about 42 kilometers.

87
00:03:57,785 --> 00:04:00,231
Thanks, Canada.
I'll take it from here.

88
00:04:00,245 --> 00:04:02,381
Barney, it's like 26 miles.

89
00:04:02,396 --> 00:04:04,322
Here's how you run a marathon.

90
00:04:04,336 --> 00:04:06,590
Step one, you start running.

91
00:04:07,166 --> 00:04:09,090
There is no step two.

92
00:04:09,577 --> 00:04:11,773
Okay, you know what? Prove it.

93
00:04:11,788 --> 00:04:13,771
Take my number and
run in my place.

94
00:04:13,788 --> 00:04:17,170
I will bet you 50 bucks you
don't even finish the race.

95
00:04:17,186 --> 00:04:18,523
50 bucks?

96
00:04:18,535 --> 00:04:22,963
Gee, Grandpa, if I win,
maybe I can buy myself
an ice-cream cone.

97
00:04:23,685 --> 00:04:25,593
Make it $10,000.

98
00:04:25,607 --> 00:04:27,952
You have a gambling problem.
You'll bet me 50.

99
00:04:27,967 --> 00:04:30,912
Fine, then no bet.
Okay, $50.

100
00:04:33,297 --> 00:04:35,680
<i>The next morning,
as the marathon began,</i>

101
00:04:35,698 --> 00:04:37,881
<i>we were focused on
Marshall's computer.</i>

102
00:04:37,897 --> 00:04:40,452
Each runner gets a tracking chip
so you can follow them online,

103
00:04:40,468 --> 00:04:43,462
see when they pass certain checkpoints.
Barney's got mine in his shoe.

104
00:04:44,028 --> 00:04:47,680
Ooh, he's starting!
This ought to be good.

105
00:04:54,057 --> 00:04:56,900
He's already passing
the second checkpoint.

106
00:04:56,995 --> 00:04:59,313
This tracking thing is amazing.

107
00:04:59,326 --> 00:05:02,172
When we get married,
you're getting one of these.

108
00:05:07,655 --> 00:05:10,443
Wow. Look at his time.
It's pretty impressive.

109
00:05:10,455 --> 00:05:13,770
He's gotta be cheating, okay.
He knew we'd check.

110
00:05:13,787 --> 00:05:15,390
Yeah, he'll do
anything to win a bet.

111
00:05:15,408 --> 00:05:18,851
Remember that time he bet me that Men
at Work sang "Hungry Like the Wolf,"

112
00:05:18,868 --> 00:05:21,460
and when he found out that they didn't,
he tried to hire them to?

113
00:05:21,528 --> 00:05:24,900
Well, it looks like, "Barney" should
be coming over the Queensboro Bridge

114
00:05:24,916 --> 00:05:28,153
and up First Avenue within
the next hour or so. But...

115
00:05:28,166 --> 00:05:30,702
there is no way that
that's really him.

116
00:05:30,878 --> 00:05:32,900
It's really him.

117
00:05:39,708 --> 00:05:41,800
Hey! That's mine.

118
00:05:41,977 --> 00:05:44,010
Yeah, you'd better run!

119
00:05:46,996 --> 00:05:50,142
- What up, non-finishers?
- Wow.

120
00:05:50,156 --> 00:05:52,442
- Very impressive, Barney.
- Right?

121
00:05:52,457 --> 00:05:54,480
Yeah, my time would have been
like a half an hour better,

122
00:05:54,515 --> 00:05:57,272
but I met this total hottie on
Mile Seven. We took a quick detour

123
00:05:57,285 --> 00:05:59,840
and had our own mini
marathon behind a Nathan's.

124
00:05:59,858 --> 00:06:01,743
I  won.

125
00:06:01,828 --> 00:06:04,630
I'm not sure anyone in
that story is a winner.

126
00:06:05,906 --> 00:06:08,000
So where's my 50 bucks?

127
00:06:08,108 --> 00:06:09,990
All right.

128
00:06:10,185 --> 00:06:13,192
I got to admit,
you earned this.

129
00:06:14,476 --> 00:06:17,990
Huh? Can't believe they haven't
made a coin for this yet.

130
00:06:18,203 --> 00:06:21,943
Anyway, I'm heading home.
Might go hit the gym.

131
00:06:22,507 --> 00:06:26,570
Oh, hey, just so you know,
uh, all marathon runners get
to use the subway
for free today.

132
00:06:26,586 --> 00:06:29,943
Wow. You know I really should
check out this "subway."

133
00:06:29,957 --> 00:06:33,691
Heard so much about it.
Wow. Look at me. Slumming it.

134
00:06:34,078 --> 00:06:36,552
Maybe I'll make a
weekend out of it

135
00:06:36,568 --> 00:06:39,043
and I'll call my bridge
and tunnel girl tonight.

136
00:06:39,105 --> 00:06:41,142
You're dating a girl
from New Jersey?

137
00:06:41,155 --> 00:06:42,983
No.

138
00:06:46,098 --> 00:06:49,172
<i>So Barney did it.
He actually finished
the marathon.</i>

139
00:06:49,395 --> 00:06:52,622
<i>But a little while later...
I got an interesting phone call.</i>

140
00:06:52,636 --> 00:06:54,331
- Hello?
- Ted, it's Barney.

141
00:06:54,348 --> 00:06:56,762
Listen to me, I need you to come
and pick me up on the subway.

142
00:06:56,798 --> 00:06:58,500
What, what are
you talking about?

143
00:06:58,516 --> 00:07:01,413
I was sitting here,
totally minding my own business.

144
00:07:01,413 --> 00:07:03,609
преди два часа

145
00:07:07,735 --> 00:07:09,600
Finisher.

146
00:07:09,918 --> 00:07:12,031
Yeah, you know what I mean.

147
00:07:12,145 --> 00:07:14,130
86th street.

148
00:07:35,856 --> 00:07:37,883
My legs don't work.

149
00:07:37,896 --> 00:07:40,910
I've already ridden the
subway twice end to end.

150
00:07:40,926 --> 00:07:43,001
I've seen where
it turns around.

151
00:07:43,037 --> 00:07:46,791
Ted, you don't ever want to see
where the subway turns around.

152
00:07:47,767 --> 00:07:50,101
Barney's legs won't work.

153
00:07:50,118 --> 00:07:53,890
He's riding the subway
from end to end
because he physically
can't get off the train.

154
00:07:53,908 --> 00:07:56,083
Best 50 bucks I ever spent.

155
00:07:56,118 --> 00:07:57,341
Listen to me, Ted.

156
00:07:57,357 --> 00:08:00,341
I'm going to lose you any second.
I'm on the fourth car of the six train

157
00:08:00,358 --> 00:08:02,663
heading south from Pelham
Bay Park in the Bronx.

158
00:08:02,675 --> 00:08:05,580
Meet me at the 86th Street station in,
like, half an hour?

159
00:08:05,595 --> 00:08:07,702
All right. I'll be right there.

160
00:08:07,715 --> 00:08:09,662
Stay where you are.

161
00:08:29,695 --> 00:08:33,493
Oh, come on. You're not even going
to give up your seat for him?

162
00:08:35,746 --> 00:08:37,642
I'm sorry. I can't.

163
00:08:37,658 --> 00:08:39,592
Douche.

164
00:08:45,691 --> 00:08:49,098
25 минути по-късно

165
00:08:54,918 --> 00:08:57,233
- Barney?!
- Ted!

166
00:09:04,538 --> 00:09:06,490
No...!

167
00:09:08,075 --> 00:09:10,380
See? If Barney never
tried to run the marathon,

168
00:09:10,397 --> 00:09:12,130
you  never would have
jumped that turnstile,

169
00:09:12,147 --> 00:09:15,883
you wouldn't have had
that court date today,
and we would have
made this flight.

170
00:09:16,045 --> 00:09:19,042
You're right.
Everything can be
traced back to him.

171
00:09:19,868 --> 00:09:21,982
Like that rash we
all got at Christmas.

172
00:09:22,987 --> 00:09:25,011
All right,
I have to see what's going on.

173
00:09:25,836 --> 00:09:28,720
- So I was able to get you two seats.
- Really? That's great!

174
00:09:28,736 --> 00:09:31,592
No, no, not you. I'm talking to
my mom about Blue Man Group.

175
00:09:31,605 --> 00:09:33,403
Ma, can I call you back?

176
00:09:33,416 --> 00:09:35,493
Okay, what about our flight?
Can we get on?

177
00:09:35,508 --> 00:09:37,591
I'm still waiting for... Huh.

178
00:09:37,778 --> 00:09:39,762
Looks like your
flight left already.

179
00:09:39,775 --> 00:09:42,390
What? No, n-n-n-no, n-no.
I have to be in Chicago today.

180
00:09:42,406 --> 00:09:44,120
Well, he never even
called you back?

181
00:09:44,138 --> 00:09:46,522
Well, it's typical pilot.
They don't call you back at work

182
00:09:46,737 --> 00:09:49,220
and they don't call you back after
you spend two nights with them

183
00:09:49,257 --> 00:09:51,240
at a Radisson in Orlando.

184
00:09:55,486 --> 00:09:58,620
<i>It turned out there was one other
flight that would just barely get me</i>

185
00:09:58,438 --> 00:10:00,500
<i>to Chicago on time
for my job interview,</i>

186
00:10:00,528 --> 00:10:03,503
<i>but it was all the way on the
other side of the airport.</i>

187
00:10:03,525 --> 00:10:05,431
What was the name of
the airline again?

188
00:10:05,448 --> 00:10:07,291
I think it was something
like Flights R' Us.

189
00:10:07,307 --> 00:10:09,753
Was the "R" backwards?
God, I hope not.

190
00:10:10,646 --> 00:10:13,181
- Geez.
- Stupid smart carts.

191
00:10:13,475 --> 00:10:15,522
More  like dumb carts.

192
00:10:15,467 --> 00:10:17,933
If we miss this flight,
it's all Barney's fault.

193
00:10:18,348 --> 00:10:21,361
You know, Barney never would have
run the marathon in the first place

194
00:10:21,376 --> 00:10:23,670
- if Marshall hadn't broken his toe.
- Yeah, so?

195
00:10:23,967 --> 00:10:25,991
What, you think
this is my fault?

196
00:10:27,186 --> 00:10:31,330
<i>For Marshall, the initial idea to run
the marathon came way back in April.</i>

197
00:10:31,347 --> 00:10:33,371
My pants are starting
to feel a little tight.

198
00:10:33,478 --> 00:10:36,970
Oh, that's okay.
I love that cute little belly.

199
00:10:41,716 --> 00:10:43,671
I cannot allow this.

200
00:10:43,685 --> 00:10:45,472
What?

201
00:10:46,185 --> 00:10:50,183
I am going to run the
New York City Marathon.

202
00:11:00,155 --> 00:11:02,793
"It is important to load
up on carbohydrates

